	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's not the same.  WRAM is extra RAM for the CPU, CHR-RAM is a replacement for CHR-ROM (for the PPU).  SMB3's tiles are in CHR-ROM, but the level map data would be unpacked to RAM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
