	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Games with CHR-RAM have their graphics stored in PRG-ROM, compressed or not. To use them, they must be copied/uncompressed to CHR-RAM. With SMB3, only the level maps are compressed in ROM, not the graphics.
<br />
<br />EDIT: Oh, Memblers already said the SMB3 part...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


