	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The iNES format has a code for classes of boards (for example the code is 4 for most boards that have an MMC3 or MMC6). It also assumes that all MMC3 games have a WRAM. Newer file formats (which you usually don't come across on warez sites) can make finer distinctions between boards, but at this stage you don't need to worry about them.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
